==English==
===Etymology===
Latin ''n&#275;penthes'' < Greek ''n&#275;penth&#275;s'' (banishing sorrow): ''n&#275;-''(not) + ''penthos'' (grief, sorrow)
===Noun===
'''nepenthe''' (also '''[[nepenthes]]''')

#A drug described in [[Homer]]'s ''[[Odyssey]]'' that relieves one of emotional pain, grief or sorrow.
#:''Quaff, oh quaff this kind nepenthe, and forget this lost Lenore''. ''[[w:The Raven|The Raven]]'' by Edgar Allen Poe (1845)
#Anything which effects the welcome forgetfulness of such sorrow.

